      "Notes": [
        {
          "Cell": "$A$1",
          "HTMLText": "Recent balances of synced accounts (Not real time updated). Negative values are credit or loans.",
          "Width": 155.25,
          "Height": 87.75
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$B$1",
          "HTMLText": "BalancesThis column shows the RECENT balance of each account. Keep in mind that ExMint won't get real time balances.",
          "Width": 133.5,
          "Height": 84
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$D$1",
          "HTMLText": "Summary of income and expenses from synced accounts. Both credit and debit are positive in this table. Expand groups to see details. See additional help on each column.",
          "Width": 154.5,
          "Height": 75.75
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$E$1",
          "HTMLText": "SubtotalShows subtotal per category in each month. Expand to see individual transaction names within a category. ",
          "Width": 154.5,
          "Height": 77.25
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$F$1",
          "HTMLText": "6M AverageShows average spending / income per category over the previous 6 months.",
          "Width": 138.75,
          "Height": 72
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$G$1",
          "HTMLText": "BudgetShows the monthly budget specified for the category in the table Budgets if a budget is available. Otherwise, just repeats the 6M Average.",
          "Width": 153,
          "Height": 92.25
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$H$1",
          "HTMLText": "RemainderCalculates the reminder (or overage) of the category budget for the selected month. Overages are presented with negative values.",
          "Width": 161.25,
          "Height": 83.25
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$J$1",
          "HTMLText": "Budgets lets you define allowances for specific spending or income categories. Then you can check on the Spending Report how much of each budget you have left or in excess. ",
          "Width": 177.75,
          "Height": 105.75
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$O$1",
          "HTMLText": "This table assists in the definition and mapping of custom Categories. Each line is a rule that will automatically assign a custom category to a group of transactions. Rules apply to previously synced as well as to future synced transactions.",
          "Width": 182.25,
          "Height": 99.75
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$D$2",
          "HTMLText": "Categories of spending / income, synced or from the Custom Categories table. Expand Years and Months to see active categories.",
          "Width": 146.25,
          "Height": 75.75
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$J$2",
          "HTMLText": "Enter here the name of a category to which the budget will be assigned. Must match one of the categories in the Spending report.",
          "Width": 165.75,
          "Height": 97.5
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$K$2",
          "HTMLText": "Select the period after which the budget will reset. You can assign a Weekly, Biweekly, Monthly, Quarterly, Biannual or Yearly budget. Exmint will calculate the montly allowance based on this field.",
          "Width": 199.5,
          "Height": 99
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$L$2",
          "HTMLText": "Enter here the amount that you want to set aside for this budget on every perdiod defined in the previous column.",
          "Width": 135,
          "Height": 84
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$M$2",
          "HTMLText": "This is a formula column that gets automatically filled with the monthly allowance corresponding to the frequency and amount columns. YOU CAN HIDE THIS COLUMN",
          "Width": 151.5,
          "Height": 92.25
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$O$2",
          "HTMLText": "The text entered in this column will be matched agains the column 'Name' in the Transactions table. Transactions that contain this text (case insensitive) in the 'Name' column will be positive matches.",
          "Width": 167.25,
          "Height": 101.25
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$P$2",
          "HTMLText": "The text entered in this column will be matched agains the column 'Categories' in the Transactions table. Transactions that contain this text (case insensitive) in the 'Categories' column will be positive matches. If you enter text in both 'Name' and 'Category' then only transactions where those strings are found in BOTH 'Name' AND 'Categories' will be positive matches.",
          "Width": 239.25,
          "Height": 110.25
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$Q$2",
          "HTMLText": "If a numeric value is present in this column, then only transactions with 'Amount' value GREATER than or equal to this value will be positive matches.",
          "Width": 161.25,
          "Height": 83.25
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$R$2",
          "HTMLText": "If a numeric value is present in this column, then only transactions with 'Amount' value SMALLER than or equal to this value will be positive matches.",
          "Width": 159,
          "Height": 72
        },
        {
          "Cell": "$S$2",
          "HTMLText": "The text in this column will be used as the 'Custom Category' value for line items in the table 'Transactions' that are positive matches to the rule in this table's line item.",
          "Width": 160.5,
          "Height": 84.75
        }
